<anmlpepl@whidbey.com>

[The number of human fatalities continues to rise with victims
ranging in age from 3 to 81 years, indicating that the availability
of effective post-exposure treatment is inadequate. The number of
fatalities now exceeds 40 compared with the 27 deaths recorded on 27
Dec 2009.

Visitors to and residents of the Indonesian island of Bali should be
aware that the problem of canine rabies is far from controlled, and
if bitten they should make their own arrangements for post-exposure
treatment.

A map of the island of Bali can be accessed at
<http://www.baliguide.com/bali_map.html>. The HealthMap/ProMED-mail
interactive map of Indonesia can be found at
<http://healthmap.org/r/00bi>.
- Mod.CP]
